ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
BASE TREK: Congressmen Dana Rohrabacher and Christopher Cox will fly an East 
Coast colleague to George Air Force Base near San Bernardino today to lobby for 
its conversion into a regional airport and a stop for the proposed Anaheim-Las 
Vegas mag-lev train. . . . The guest is Robert Torricelli, a New Jersey 
Democrat who chairs a house science and technology subcommittee. "He may be 
able to help us with federal permits and right-of-way issues," Rohrabacher 
said. . . . The three will breakfast first in Newport Beach with developer Buck 
Johns, a mag-lev and airport promoter who owns land near the base. Jerry Hicks 
and Jeffrey A. Perlman 
